d", "value": "NOTSET", "display_name": "Social distancing enforced throughout experience"}, {"name": "regularly_sanitized", "value": "NOTSET", "display_name": "Regularly sanitized high-traffic areas"}, {"name": "equipment_sanitized", "value": "NOTSET", "display_name": "Gear/equipment sanitized between use"}, {"name": "transportation_vehicles_sanitized", "value": "NOTSET", "display_name": "Transportation vehicles regularly sanitized"}, {"name": "guides_required_to_wash_hands", "value": "NOTSET", "display_name": "Guides required to wash hands"}, {"name": "temperature_checks_for_staff", "value": "NOTSET", "display_name": "Regular temperature checks for staff"}, {"name": "temperature_checks_for_travelers", "value": "NOTSET", "display_name": "Temperature checks for travelers upon arrival"}, {"name": "contactless_payments_for_extras", "value": "NOTSET", "display_name": "Contactless payments for gratuities and add-ons"}]}, "pickup_on_request": 0, "redemption_method": "", "suitable_for_solo": 0, "from_price_display": "&#8364;21", "last_bookable_date": "2026-12-12", "next_bookable_date": "2026-05-22", "supplier_tour_code": "PALISIS_55_12573", "cancellation_policy": "", "geocode_start_point": {"label": "Casino Luxembourg", "geocode": "49.609800,6.127140", "loc_relation": 1, "google_place_id": "ChIJFUuwwdRIlUcR2aUvaQ0ROGY"}, "suitable_for_groups": 0, "suitable_for_couples": 0, "suitable_for_business": 0, "suitable_for_children": 0, "suitable_for_students": 0, "default_departure_size": 20, "from_price_apr_display": "&#8364;0", "from_price_aug_display": "&#8364;21", "from_price_dec_display": "&#8364;21", "from_price_feb_display": "&#8364;0", "from_price_jan_display": "&#8364;0", "from_price_jul_display": "&#8364;21", "from_price_jun_display": "&#8364;21", "from_price_mar_display": "&#8364;0", "from_price_may_display": "&#8364;21", "from_price_nov_display": "&#8364;21", "from_price_oct_display": "&#8364;21", "from_price_sep_display": "&#8364;21", "tour_permit_child_only": 1, "distribution_identifier": "SI_12846_24", "suitable_for_wheelchairs": 0, "tour_departure_structure": {"type": "NOTSET"}, "descriptions_last_updated": "2026-05-19"}	2026-05-22 07:25:16.447+00	palisis	\N	\N	2026-05-21 11:28:21.572584+00	2026-05-23 04:21:21.746289+00	Day tour/trip/activity/attraction - No overnight stay	4	Independent / Self-drive	All ages / Not applicable	No accommodation / Not applicable	{museums}	{nl,en,fr,de,lb}	Casino Luxembourg	49.609800,6.127140	Villa Vauban	49.612997,6.122483	LU	MEDIUM	Fancy a cultural excursion during which you can collect steps at the same time? As part of our collaboration with the “Staater Museeën” group, we have created a beautiful walking tour that connects the 7 museums of Luxembourg City	<strong>Ready for a 6 km walk through Luxembourg City?</strong>\nWalk the Mile: 7 museums of the capital is an immersive journey that will ignite your curiosity and captivate your senses. Discover the rich cultural heritage housed within the walls of these diverse museums and embark on a memorable exploration of art, history, and innovation. Unearth hidden treasures, delve into captivating exhibits, and expand your horizons as you walk through the corridors of knowledge. Don’t miss this extraordinary opportunity to immerse yourself in the captivating world of museums.  \n\n<strong>Museums mile – make your own way to the museums</strong>\nAlong the way, you will discover remarkable places and tourist attractions. The route includes 7 stops corresponding to the 7 museums of Luxembourg City. Since your ticket is valid for 48 hours, you can schedule the museum visits over the two days as you wish. Before booking your ticket, beware of the opening days and time of each museum.  \n\nThe walk will take you to the most important museums of the city, including:\n\n<strong> 1) Casino Luxembourg – Contemporary Art Forum (closed on Tuesday)</strong>\n\n<strong>2) Lëtzebuerg City Museum (closed on Monday)</strong>\nThis museum located on the ancient Fish market, which square also contains the same name, is a museum that tells the story of the city’s development form its origins as a Roman settlement to its current status as a modern European capital.\n\n<strong>3) National History Museum (closed on Monday)</strong>\nThis museum is located in  a stunning buidling that houses a large collection dedicated to archaeological artifacts, artworks and historical objects. Delve into Luxembourg’s past history of art and learn about the development from prehistoric times to the present day.\n\n<strong>4) MUDAM Luxembourg (closed on Tuesday)</strong>\nThe MUDAM is a contemporary art museums located in the modern and financial district of Kirchberg, in  futuristic building desine dby Ieoah Ming Pei. This museums exhibits contemporary pieces of art\n\n<strong>5) Museum Dräi Eechelen (closed on Monday)</strong>\nThe Dräi Eechelen is located in a restored fortress overlooking the city. This museum focuses on Luxembourg’s military history and presents exhibitions on topics such as the fortress’s construction, the ole of the military and facts about war on the country.\n\n<strong>6) National Museum of History and Art (closed on Monday)</strong>\nThis museums provides an immersive experience by showcasing the city’s history through multimedia presentations, photographs and interactive displays. All temporary exhibitions are not included in this ticket.\n\n<strong>7) Villa Vauban (closed on Tuesday / 1st November / 25th December / 1st January)</strong>\nThis museums is focused on European Art, from the 17th to 21st century, with an emphasis on Luxembourgish artists.  \n\n <strong>How to download the Museums mile?</strong>\nAdmission to these 7 museums is included in the price. After downloading the app sightseeing.lu and purchasing this tour, you will find 36 points on the interactive map displayed on your screen, which will be explained by text and audio. These points of interest correspond to historical buildings, landmarks, parks and more. Your smartphone will be transformed into a city guide!  \n\nOverall, the Walk The Mile and the 7 museums in Luxembourg City offers a comprehensive and captivating exploration of the city’s history, culture and art. Whether you are a history lover, an art enthusiast, or simply someone eager to learn more about Luxembourg, this tour provides a unique and enriching experience that will leave you with lasting memories	* Entry to the 7 museums of Luxembourg City,\n* A cultural and sporty activity combined.\n* For lovers of art and culture	{"36 POI’s to read or listen to via the sightseeing.lu app","Access to the 7 museums","Access to the sightseeing.lu app with an interactive GPS localized map, audio and text on POI’s","Offline functioning of the app"}	{Headphones,"Temporary exhibitions in the museums"}	Bring your own headphones (if needed),\nValidity of this offer: 48 hours,\nRemember to charge your smartphone before starting your experience,\nDownload the purchased tour beforehand (online mode),\nIf you are interested in visiting a temporary exhibition in a specific museum, please visit the relevant website for more information,\nCheck the closing days of the museums on the offer description,\nDuring the Museum Days, the entrance is for free	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	1	10	f	2026-05-22	2026-12-12
tcms_5	5	Nature & Castle Day Tour	\N	Immerse yourself in the enchanting beauty of Luxembourg with our enchanting Nature and Castles Day Tour through Luxembourg. This captivating experience combines the breathtaking landscapes of the countryside with the rich history and grandeur of Luxembourg’s regions	\N	115.00	\N	8 hours	Tours	{}	Boulevard de la Pétrusse/Place de Metz	Sightseeing.lu	https://cdn.tourcms.com/a/12846/5/1/large.jpg	{https://cdn.tourcms.com/a/12846/5/1/large.jpg}	{"Learn more about Luxembourg's nature and history","Explore the Mullerthal trail and the Schiessentümpel waterfall","Visit the city of Vianden and its medieval castle","Discover the old town of Echternach"}	\N	0.00	0	https://live.tourcms.com/reserve/r1.php?t=5&a=12846&w=13407&people=1&ty=t&k=5140fec80f80	\N	f	f	published	{"ex": "* Lunch \\n* Drinks", "exp": "* Learn more about Luxembourg's nature and history\\n* Explore the Mullerthal trail and the Schiessentümpel waterfall\\n* Visit the city of Vianden and its medieval castle\\n* Discover the old town of Echternach", "inc": "* 8-hour tour\\n* Audio Guide in 3 languages (EN, FR, DE)\\n* Fixed schedule with visits to the Schiessentümpel waterfall\\n* Entry ticket to the castle in Vianden (not guided)", "grade": 1, "has_d": 1, "has_f": 0, "has_h": 0, "cutoff": {"type": "before_start_sec", "value": 0}, "images": {"image": [{"url": "https://cdn.tourcms.com/a/12846/5/1/default.jpg", "image_id": 1, "url_large": "https://cdn.tourcms.com/a/12846/5/1/large.jpg", "@_thumbnail": "true", "url_thumbnail": "https://cdn.tourcms.com/a/12846/5/1/thumbnail.jpg"}]}, "inc_ex": "* 8-hour tour\\n* Audio Guide in 3 languages (EN, FR, DE)\\n* Fixed schedule with visits to the Schiessentümpel waterfall\\n* Entry ticket to the castle in Vianden (not guided)", "redeem": "* Meeting Point: Luxembourg, Spuerkeess, 2330 Ville-Haute Luxembourg\\n* Please be 10 minutes in advance at the meeting point.\\n* In case of delay or problems, please call the following number: +352 266 51 2250", "country": "LU", "summary": "Nature and castles tour in Luxembourg", "tour_id": 5, "book_url": "https://live.tourcms.com/reserve/r1.php?t=5&a=12846&w=13407&people=1&ty=t&k=5140fec80f80", "duration": 1, "end_time": "09:30", "has_sale": 1, "location": "Boulevard de la Pétrusse/Place de Metz", "longdesc": "Embark on a journey through lush green valleys, meandering rivers, and picturesque forests that showcase Luxembourg’s natural wonders. Witness the harmonious coexistence of nature and architecture as you explore stunning castles nestled within this idyllic setting. Our friendly driver will gladly drive you throughout the scenic landscapes of our beautiful country.\\n\\nWith the help of the informative audio guides in the bus, learn about the remarkable stories of the past that have shaped the region into what it is today. Indulge your senses as you step into centuries-old castles (Beaufort and Vianden) filled with opulent interiors, intricate details, and breathtaking views. Imagine yourself transported back in time as you stroll through elegant halls, marvel at stunning artwork, and discover hidden treasures within these architectural marvels. Throughout the tour, you’ll have ample opportunities to capture unforgettable moments amidst the stunning natural landscapes and breathtaking castle backdrops. Whether you’re a history enthusiast, nature lover, or simply seeking a day of exploration and relaxation, this spectacular sightseeing visit promises a truly unforgettable experience.  \\n\\nSo, embark on this captivating journey and let us take you on a magical adventure through the heart of Luxembourg’s captivating nature and majestic castles. Book your Nature and Castle Day Tour soon and discover the beauty and charm that awaits you in this exceptional destination", "priority": "MEDIUM", "tour_url": "https://sightseeing.lu//trip/nature-and-castles-of-luxembourg-8-hour-day-tour/", "validity": {"validity_type": "NOT SET", "validity_value": 0, "validity_minutes": 0}, "available": "Check Availability Calendar", "documents": "", "essential": "* Please note the the Beaufort Castle remains closed from November until end of March", "itinerary": "10:00 – 10:45: Mullerthal trail and Schiessentümpel waterfall\\nThe waterfall, known as Schiessentümpel, with its three water jets on the Black Ernz is one of the most photographed motives of the Mullerthal Region, Luxembourg’s Little Switzerland. This is a 45-minute walking tour. Please make sure to wear comfortable hiking shoes, especially at the Schiessentümpel waterfall.\\n\\n11:00: Beaufort Castle (Closed from November until March)\\nOne stop at Beaufort to take some photos and admire the view. During Spring and Summer season, the Beaufort Castle is open to the public.\\n\\n 12:00 – 14:00: Vianden Castle – An outstanding monument\\nThe small medieval town of Vianden attracts thousands of visitors every year. Particularly worth seeing are the imposing castle that overlooks the town, the town wall with its fortified towers and Luxembourg’s only chairlift. During our stop you have 2 hours of free time that you can plan for yourself. We recommend that you bring a lunch or snack if you don’t want to waste time in a restaurant, otherwise the time might be too short.\\n\\n 15:15 – 16:00: The old town of Echternach\\nEchternach is the oldest town in Luxembourg and was founded in 698 by the Benedictine monk Willibrord. Visit the most beautiful places and buildings of Echternach, like the Basilica, the abbey and the market. After Echternach, we will return to the departure point in Luxembourg City", "shortdesc": "Immerse yourself in the enchanting beauty of Luxembourg with our enchanting Nature and Castles Day Tour through Luxembourg. This captivating experience combines the breathtaking landscapes of the countryside with the rich history and grandeur of Luxembourg’s regions", "time_type": "strict", "tour_name": "Nature & Castle Day Tour", "tour_tags": {"tag": [{"text": "Activity is sui