e  popular  landmarks like the Casemates du Bock and the Notre-Dame Cathedral, and enjoy the scenic views of Luxembourg City!\n\n To conclude, Luxembourg City boasts several landmarks and UNESCO world heritage sites that offer a glimpse into rich history and cultural significance. From the well-preserved fortifications to the architectural wonders and vibrant squares, these sites are a testament to the city’s past and present. Exploring all these lovely places and green parks in Luxembourg City is a truly enriching experience for any visitor.  \n\n Whether you’d like to ride in the city or in nature, our e-bikes are perfect to escape everyday life, whether alone or in good company. Luxembourg offers a multitude of cycling paths in the city center or on public parks. Don’t hesitate to contact us for advice during the booking procedure. You can also find more information about the guided e-Bike tours on www.sightseeing.lu	* Rental of powerful E-Bikes\n* Move freely and flexibly through our beautiful capital city\n* Different sizes are available\n* Helmets and locks are provided	{"E-Bike rental (half-day or full-day)",Helmet}	{"Food & drinks",Snacks,"Children e-bike and seats (on demand for a fee)"}	* If you booked the full-day rental, we ask you to bring the e-bikes before 17:00 (5 pm)	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	1	10	f	2026-05-22	2026-12-31
