couples": 0, "suitable_for_business": 0, "suitable_for_children": 0, "suitable_for_students": 0, "default_departure_size": 12, "from_price_apr_display": "&#8364;0", "from_price_aug_display": "&#8364;90", "from_price_dec_display": "&#8364;0", "from_price_feb_display": "&#8364;0", "from_price_jan_display": "&#8364;0", "from_price_jul_display": "&#8364;90", "from_price_jun_display": "&#8364;90", "from_price_mar_display": "&#8364;0", "from_price_may_display": "&#8364;90", "from_price_nov_display": "&#8364;90", "from_price_oct_display": "&#8364;90", "from_price_sep_display": "&#8364;90", "tour_permit_child_only": 0, "distribution_identifier": "SI_12846_8", "suitable_for_wheelchairs": 0, "tour_departure_structure": {"type": "SINGLE", "start_times": {"time": "10:45"}, "add_new_auto": 1, "departure_types": ""}, "descriptions_last_updated": "2026-05-19"}	2026-05-22 07:25:13.805+00	palisis	\N	\N	2026-05-12 12:31:17.631608+00	2026-05-22 07:25:13.806863+00	Day tour/trip/activity/attraction - No overnight stay	4	Guided (tour guide / driver)	All ages / Not applicable	No accommodation / Not applicable	{food,operator-direct-product}	{en,fr,de}	Place de Paris	49.603548,6.131077	Place de Paris	49.603548,6.131077	LU	MEDIUM	Stroll through the heart of the vibrant Luxembourg City, indulging in a culinary adventure that will awaken your taste buds and immerse in the local culture	Embark on a delightful journey through the paved streets of Luxembourg City, guided by our passionate local guide who will lead you to the hidden gems and to some gastronomical hot-spots in the capital. As you traverse the city’s charming neighborhoods, you’ll discover the fusion of traditional Luxembourgish cuisine with French, German, and Belgian influences, creating a symphony of taste on your palate.\n\n Prepare to indulge in a multitude of mouth-watering delights, from typical Luxembourg dishes such as Rieslingspaschtéit, a meat pie filled with a Riesling white wine jelly, to refined local ham accompanied by a glass of one of the best crémants or Riesling wine in the country by Domaine Alice Hartmann. In the middle of the food tour, you will follow your guide to another delicious tasting: a quiche Lorraine prepared with local ingredients by one of the most famous delicatessen shop in Luxembourg. After that, you can treat yourself to a delicious chocolate and sweets tasting at a finest Luxembourgish Chocolaterie.\n\n Finally, let’s not forget the famous Kniddelen, flour quenelles with a creamy sauce and smoked bacon, a symbol of comfort food so much loved by the population	* Combine a walking tour together with a gastronomic experience\n* Taste the best of Luxembourgish food\n* Discover regional food at local shops	{"Professional guide","Guided visit of 3 hours","5 tasting stops","Food tasting at local shops"}	{"Drinks (at the customer’s expense)","Additional food"}	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	1	10	f	2026-05-23	2026-11-28
