 "fields": {"field": {"name": "start_time", "value": "15:15"}}, "partial": 0}, {"label": "{\\"en\\":\\"75 Min Tour\\"}", "active": 1, "fields": {"field": {"name": "start_time", "value": "12:15"}}, "partial": 0}, {"label": "{\\"en\\":\\"75 Min Tour\\"}", "active": 1, "fields": {"field": {"name": "start_time", "value": "16:00"}}, "partial": 0}, {"label": "[]", "active": 1, "fields": {"field": {"name": "start_time", "value": "14:00"}}, "partial": 0}]}}, "descriptions_last_updated": "2026-05-19"}	2026-05-22 07:25:11.978+00	palisis	\N	\N	2026-05-12 12:31:20.479888+00	2026-05-22 07:25:11.979822+00	Day tour/trip/activity/attraction - No overnight stay	4	Independent / Self-drive	All ages / Not applicable	No accommodation / Not applicable	{day-trips,suitable-for-solo,operator-direct-product}	{nl,en,fr,de,lb}	Banque et Caisse d'Epargne de l'Etat (BCEE), SPUERKEESS	49.607274,6.128675	Banque et Caisse d'Epargne de l'Etat (BCEE), SPUERKEESS	49.607274,6.128675	LU	MEDIUM	Immerse into the beauty of Luxembourg’s capital city and explore the hidden gems on board of our sightseeing cozy minibus. Listen to an audio guide and admire the historic landmarks and architecture as well as the vibrant and modern side of the city	<strong>Step on the immersive Luxembourg City Bus Tour!</strong>\nImmerse into the beauty of Luxembourg’s capital city and unveil hidden gems and  historical landmarks on board of this sightseeing cozy minibus. The Luxembourg City Bus Tour offers you a convenient and immersive way to discover the rich history, stunning architecture, and vibrant culture of our beautiful green capital during the whole time of the year. Do you wish to see all the highlights in the city? Book your seats now.\n<strong>About the Luxembourg City Bus Tour</strong>\nThroughout the tour, you will be provided with informative content with the help of a high-quality and enriching audio guide, sharing historical facts about the city’s past and present. The bus is equipped with comfortable seating, air-conditioning, and large windows, ensuring you’ll have the best view to capture the best pictures. This city bus tour doesn’t include any stops, however it offers an ideal introduction to Luxembourg’s unique blend of old-modern charm and contemporary energy. Whether you’re a first-time visitor or a seasoned traveler, you’ll gain deeper appreciation for our little European gem!	* Embark on a sightseeing tour through Luxembourg city.\n* Listen to commentary from the audio guide and learn about the city's history.\n* Blend into a mix of old and new architecture.\n* Explore the vibrant area and unveil hidden gems	{"Audio guide (5 languages)",Headphones}	{"Live Guide"}	* Please wait for the driver’s permission before you enter the bus and show him/her your ticket. \n* This bus tour is not a Hop on Hop off and has no stops included. \n* Baby strollers and wheelchairs are not allowed in ths bus.  \n* We don’t take any responsibility on baby strollers	\N	\N	\N	\N	<strong>Luxembourg City Bus Tour itinerary</strong>\nUnveil hidden gems and immerse yourself in the captivating beauty of Luxembourg’s capital city with the Luxembourg City Bus Tour. Discover historical landmarks, stunning architecture, and vibrant culture on this convenient and immersive sightseeing experience.  Depart from the Boulevard de la Pétrusse, near Spuerkeess  HQ with our Luxembourg City Bus Tour. Then, you will be driven along the avenue de la Liberte at the Quartier de la Gare. Gare is a simple neighbourhood and a bustling transport hub that encompasses Luxembourg station, near which hotels and chain stores are grouped together.\n\nThen, our driver takes you along the Constitution square, where you can marvel the famous Gëlle Fra statue, the remembrance memorial. Among other monuments, you also see the Malakoff Tower, an important monument built as part of the fortress in 1861. This tower has been fully restored and is now the new headquarters of Scouting in Luxembourg asbl. You pass over the Viaduct, also known as Old Bridge.\n\nIn just a few seconds, you are entering the city’s business district: Kirchberg. Before that, you will have a chance to see the panoramic elevator and the Pfaffenthal district just before entering the Kirchberg Plateau. Admire the skyscrapers and the splendor of a district rich in architecture. Take a photo of the Luxembourg Philharmonie and don’t miss a visit at the Grand-Duc Jean Museum of Modern Art (Mudam) after your city bus tour	\N	\N	\N	\N	1	10	f	2026-05-22	2026-10-31
tcms_7	7	City Train discover the old City of Luxembourg	\N	Onboard our City Train in the old town Luxembourg, explore the charming beauty of Luxembourg City. Immerse yourself in the rich history and vibrant culture as you traverse the narrow streets and admire the picturesque architecture	\N	13.00	\N	50 min	Tours	{}	Luxembourg	Sightseeing.lu	https://cdn.tourcms.com/a/12846/7/1/large.jpg	{https://cdn.tourcms.com/a/12846/7/1/large.jpg}	{"Discover the old town of Luxembourg","Passage in Rives de Clausen, the heart of Luxembourg's nightlife","A real highlight for kids and grown ups","For history and architecture lovers"}	\N	0.00	0	https://live.tourcms.com/reserve/r1.php?t=7&a=12846&w=13407&people=1&ty=t&k=2b4a1b50a8d1	\N	f	f	published	{"ex": "* Live Guide", "exp": "* Discover the old town of Luxembourg\\n* Passage in Rives de Clausen, the heart of Luxembourg's nightlife\\n* A real highlight for kids and grown ups\\n* For history and architecture lovers", "inc": "* Tour on the City Train \\n* Headphones \\n* Audio guide in 7 languages", "rest": "* Wheelchairs and baby strollers are not allowed in the City Train. \\n* Please note that we don’t take any responsibility on baby strollers", "grade": 1, "has_d": 1, "has_f": 0, "has_h": 0, "cutoff": {"type": "before_start_sec", "value": 0}, "images": {"image": [{"url": "https://cdn.tourcms.com/a/12846/7/1/default.jpg", "image_id": 1, "url_large": "https://cdn.tourcms.com/a/12846/7/1/large.jpg", "@_thumbnail": "true", "url_thumbnail": "https://cdn.tourcms.com/a/12846/7/1/thumbnail.jpg"}]}, "inc_ex": "* Tour on the City Train \\n* Headphones \\n* Audio guide in 7 languages", "redeem": "* Departure is at Um Bock, near the entrance of the Bock Casemates. \\n* Wheelchairs and baby strollers are not allowed in the City Train. \\n* Please note that we don’t take any responsibility on baby strollers. \\n* Contact us: +352 266 51 – 2200/2250 or  hello@sightseeing.lu", "country": "LU", "summary": "Luxembourg old town train tour 50 min", "tour_id": 7, "book_url": "https://live.tourcms.com/reserve/r1.php?t=7&a=12846&w=13407&people=1&ty=t&k=2b4a1b50a8d1", "duration": 1, "end_time": "MULTI", "has_sale": 1, "location": "Luxembourg", "longdesc": "Are you passionate about history and culture, about the Grand Duchy of Luxembourg? A small country but with a great history… Discover the history of the former “Gibraltar of the North” which revives while driving through the historical sites of the Old Fortress in our City Train. Travel with us to the past to better understand the present.  \\n\\nThe city train in the Old Town Luxembourg offers a charming and convenient way to explore this historic area. As it winds its way through the cobbled streets and narrow alleyways, passengers are treated to panoramic views of medieval architecture, fortified walls, and picturesque squares. The train journey serves as a captivating journey through time, allowing passengers to immerse themselves in the rich history and cultural heritage of Luxembourg’s Old Town. Knowledgeable audio guides provide insightful commentary, sharing stories of the city’s past and attractions along the route.  \\n \\nThe rhythmic chug of the train, coupled with the gentle sway of its carriages, creates a relaxed and unhurried atmosphere, perfect for leisurely sightseeing. Passengers can hop on and off at designated stops, allowing them to explore key points of interest at their own pace. Whether it’s admiring the grandeur of the Casemates, marveling at the intricate carvings of Notre-Dame Cathedral, or strolling along the scenic promenade of the Alzette River, the city train offers a unique and enchanting way to experience the Old Town of Luxembourg. With its nostalgic charm and informative narration, it promises an unforgettable journey through this UNESCO World Heritage site", "priority": "MEDIUM", "tour_url": "https://sightseeing.lu/trip/city-train-in-the-old-town-of-luxembourg/", "validity": {"validity_type": "NOT SET", "validity_value": 0, "