n in the old town Luxembourg, explore the charming beauty of Luxembourg City. Immerse yourself in the rich history and vibrant culture as you traverse the narrow streets and admire the picturesque architecture	Are you passionate about history and culture, about the Grand Duchy of Luxembourg? A small country but with a great history… Discover the history of the former “Gibraltar of the North” which revives while driving through the historical sites of the Old Fortress in our City Train. Travel with us to the past to better understand the present.  \n\nThe city train in the Old Town Luxembourg offers a charming and convenient way to explore this historic area. As it winds its way through the cobbled streets and narrow alleyways, passengers are treated to panoramic views of medieval architecture, fortified walls, and picturesque squares. The train journey serves as a captivating journey through time, allowing passengers to immerse themselves in the rich history and cultural heritage of Luxembourg’s Old Town. Knowledgeable audio guides provide insightful commentary, sharing stories of the city’s past and attractions along the route.  \n \nThe rhythmic chug of the train, coupled with the gentle sway of its carriages, creates a relaxed and unhurried atmosphere, perfect for leisurely sightseeing. Passengers can hop on and off at designated stops, allowing them to explore key points of interest at their own pace. Whether it’s admiring the grandeur of the Casemates, marveling at the intricate carvings of Notre-Dame Cathedral, or strolling along the scenic promenade of the Alzette River, the city train offers a unique and enchanting way to experience the Old Town of Luxembourg. With its nostalgic charm and informative narration, it promises an unforgettable journey through this UNESCO World Heritage site	* Discover the old town of Luxembourg\n* Passage in Rives de Clausen, the heart of Luxembourg's nightlife\n* A real highlight for kids and grown ups\n* For history and architecture lovers	{"Tour on the City Train",Headphones,"Audio guide in 7 languages"}	{"Live Guide"}	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	1	10	f	2026-05-22	2026-11-15
tcms_9	9	Best Walking Tour in Luxembourg City	\N	Immerse yourself in the beauty of Luxembourg City with our unforgettable guided walking tour. If your time in Luxembourg is limited, then this 2,5-hour guided walking tour offers sufficient opportunity to appreciate the city’s charm	\N	25.00	\N	2.5 hours	Tours	{}	Luxembourg	Sightseeing.lu	https://cdn.tourcms.com/a/12846/9/1/large.jpg	{https://cdn.tourcms.com/a/12846/9/1/large.jpg}	{"Discover the historic center of the city and its highlights.","Learn about secret locations only locals know.","Get some insights into history, people, and culture"}	\N	0.00	0	https://live.tourcms.com/reserve/r1.php?t=9&a=12846&w=13407&people=1&ty=t&k=bb9a7d3302cc	\N	f	f	published	{"ex": "* Tips", "exp": "* Discover the historic center of the city and its highlights.\\n* Learn about secret locations only locals know.\\n* Get some insights into history, people, and culture", "inc": "* Local Guide \\n* Sweet delight", "grade": 1, "has_d": 1, "has_f": 0, "has_h": 0, "cutoff": {"type": "before_start_sec", "value": 720}, "images": {"image": [{"url": "https://cdn.tourcms.com/a/12846/9/1/default.jpg", "image_id": 1, "url_large": "https://cdn.tourcms.com/a/12846/9/1/large.jpg", "@_thumbnail": "true", "url_thumbnail": "https://cdn.tourcms.com/a/12846/9/1/thumbnail.jpg"}]}, "inc_ex": "* Local Guide \\n* Sweet delight", "redeem": "* Our tours are in English! If you wish a different language, please contact us at hello@sightseeing.lu. T\\n* Be 10 minutes earlier at the meeting point. Meeting Point: Place Guillaume II at the William Statue", "country": "LU", "summary": "Explore Luxembourg on a 2.5-hour guided tour", "tour_id": 9, "book_url": "https://live.tourcms.com/reserve/r1.php?t=9&a=12846&w=13407&people=1&ty=t&k=bb9a7d3302cc", "duration": 1, "end_time": "MULTI", "has_sale": 1, "location": "Luxembourg", "longdesc": "Our tour starts at Place Guillaume II, at the William II statue, a bustling square surrounded by cafes and restaurants. This vibrant hub is perfect for relaxation and people-watching. Indulge in some local cuisine or refreshments as you reflect on the rich tapestry of Luxembourg’s past and present. You will be introduced to captivating tales about the establishment of the Grand Duchy and its visionary founder, Sigfrid. As the guide continues its storytelling, marvel at the Grand-Ducal Palace, with its impressive facade and changing of the guard ceremony. While the interior is not open to the public, the exterior alone is a testament to Luxembourg’s regal history.  \\n\\nMoving on, we’ll see the Notre-Dame Cathedral, a magnificent Gothic masterpiece. Admire the intricate stained glass windows and the sculpted beauty of this centuries-old cathedral. The interior is equally awe-inspiring, with its vaulted ceilings and historical artifacts. The next segment of our tour takes us to the Corniche, often referred to as the “most beautiful balcony in Europe.” This elevated promenade offers breathtaking views of the Alzette Valley and the ancient city below. Take a moment to soak in the panoramic scenery and appreciate the unique layout of Luxembourg City.  \\n\\nThe guide will also delve into the language’s origins and shed light on the fascinating underground tunnels known as “the Casemates.” Furthermore, the guide will regale you with amusing anecdotes, local legends, and provide insights into the city’s contemporary lifestyle. In the course of this guided tour, you’ll get the chance to have a sweet tasting at a local partner… the rest keeps a surprise !\\n\\nFeel free to inquire about any queries you may have as the guide endeavors to address them. In the end, we will be back in the city center from where you can continue your own visit and go to the photo spot Luxembourg City Walls: Chemin de la Corniche", "priority": "MEDIUM", "tour_url": "https://sightseeing.lu/trip/best-guided-walking-tour-in-luxembourg-city/", "validity": {"validity_type": "NOT SET", "validity_value": 0, "validity_minutes": 0}, "av