nd sanitizer available to travelers and staff"}, {"name": "social_distancing_enforced", "value": "NOTSET", "display_name": "Social distancing enforced throughout experience"}, {"name": "regularly_sanitized", "value": "NOTSET", "display_name": "Regularly sanitized high-traffic areas"}, {"name": "equipment_sanitized", "value": "NOTSET", "display_name": "Gear/equipment sanitized between use"}, {"name": "transportation_vehicles_sanitized", "value": "NOTSET", "display_name": "Transportation vehicles regularly sanitized"}, {"name": "guides_required_to_wash_hands", "value": "NOTSET", "display_name": "Guides required to wash hands"}, {"name": "temperature_checks_for_staff", "value": "NOTSET", "display_name": "Regular temperature checks for staff"}, {"name": "temperature_checks_for_travelers", "value": "NOTSET", "display_name": "Temperature checks for travelers upon arrival"}, {"name": "contactless_payments_for_extras", "value": "NOTSET", "display_name": "Contactless payments for gratuities and add-ons"}]}, "pickup_on_request": 0, "redemption_method": "", "suitable_for_solo": 0, "from_price_display": "&#8364;25", "last_bookable_date": "2026-12-31", "next_bookable_date": "2026-05-22", "supplier_tour_code": "PALISIS_55_9646", "cancellation_policy": "", "geocode_start_point": {"label": "Place Guillaume II - Knuedler", "geocode": "49.610642,6.130970", "loc_relation": 0, "google_place_id": "ChIJIbwtNNNIlUcR9p7eIqgFQeQ"}, "suitable_for_groups": 0, "suitable_for_couples": 0, "suitable_for_business": 0, "suitable_for_children": 0, "suitable_for_students": 0, "default_departure_size": 20, "from_price_apr_display": "&#8364;0", "from_price_aug_display": "&#8364;25", "from_price_dec_display": "&#8364;25", "from_price_feb_display": "&#8364;0", "from_price_jan_display": "&#8364;0", "from_price_jul_display": "&#8364;25", "from_price_jun_display": "&#8364;25", "from_price_mar_display": "&#8364;0", "from_price_may_display": "&#8364;25", "from_price_nov_display": "&#8364;25", "from_price_oct_display": "&#8364;25", "from_price_sep_display": "&#8364;25", "tour_permit_child_only": 0, "distribution_identifier": "SI_12846_9", "suitable_for_wheelchairs": 0, "tour_departure_structure": {"type": "SINGLE", "start_times": {"time": "14:00"}, "add_new_auto": 1, "departure_types": ""}, "descriptions_last_updated": "2026-05-19"}	2026-05-22 07:25:13.135+00	palisis	\N	\N	2026-05-12 12:31:18.09697+00	2026-05-22 07:25:13.136133+00	Day tour/trip/activity/attraction - No overnight stay	4	Guided (tour guide / driver)	All ages / Not applicable	No accommodation / Not applicable	{walking-tours,operator-direct-product}	{en,fr,de}	Place Guillaume II - Knuedler	49.610642,6.130970	Place Guillaume II - Knuedler	49.610642,6.130970	LU	MEDIUM	Immerse yourself in the beauty of Luxembourg City with our unforgettable guided walking tour. If your time in Luxembourg is limited, then this 2,5-hour guided walking tour offers sufficient opportunity to appreciate the city’s charm	Our tour starts at Place Guillaume II, at the William II statue, a bustling square surrounded by cafes and restaurants. This vibrant hub is perfect for relaxation and people-watching. Indulge in some local cuisine or refreshments as you reflect on the rich tapestry of Luxembourg’s past and present. You will be introduced to captivating tales about the establishment of the Grand Duchy and its visionary founder, Sigfrid. As the guide continues its storytelling, marvel at the Grand-Ducal Palace, with its impressive facade and changing of the guard ceremony. While the interior is not open to the public, the exterior alone is a testament to Luxembourg’s regal history.  \n\nMoving on, we’ll see the Notre-Dame Cathedral, a magnificent Gothic masterpiece. Admire the intricate stained glass windows and the sculpted beauty of this centuries-old cathedral. The interior is equally awe-inspiring, with its vaulted ceilings and historical artifacts. The next segment of our tour takes us to the Corniche, often referred to as the “most beautiful balcony in Europe.” This elevated promenade offers breathtaking views of the Alzette Valley and the ancient city below. Take a moment to soak in the panoramic scenery and appreciate the unique layout of Luxembourg City.  \n\nThe guide will also delve into the language’s origins and shed light on the fascinating underground tunnels known as “the Casemates.” Furthermore, the guide will regale you with amusing anecdotes, local legends, and provide insights into the city’s contemporary lifestyle. In the course of this guided tour, you’ll get the chance to have a sweet tasting at a local partner… the rest keeps a surprise !\n\nFeel free to inquire about any queries you may have as the guide endeavors to address them. In the end, we will be back in the city center from where you can continue your own visit and go to the photo spot Luxembourg City Walls: Chemin de la Corniche	* Discover the historic center of the city and its highlights.\n* Learn about secret locations only locals know.\n* Get some insights into history, people, and culture	{"Local Guide","Sweet delight"}	{Tips}	* Please bring:  Bottle of water, Umbrella (in case of rain) & Comfortable shoes.\n* This tour is dog-friendly. \n* Wheelchair accessible. \n* For baby carriages there might be some obstacles like stairs and steep streets	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	1	10	f	2026-05-22	2026-12-31
tcms_13	13	E-Bike Tour: The Best of Luxembourg in 3 hours	\N	On this guided tour, we take you to discover the capital’s main points of interest by electric bike. The tour includes some very steep slopes, which is why it is important to be accompanied by an experienced guide	\N	76.00	\N	3 hours	Tours	{}	Luxemburg	Sightseeing.lu	https://cdn.tourcms.com/a/12846/13/1/xlarge.jpg	{https://cdn.tourcms.com/a/12846/13/1/xlarge.jpg}	{"Discover the hotspots of Luxembourg City.","A fun experience, suitable for all levels.","A combination of Luxembourg's history and modern side"}	\N	0.00	0	https://live.tourcms.com/reserve/r1.php?t=13&a=12846&w=13407&people=1&ty=t&k=34360731a15e	\N	f	f	published	{"ex": "* Drinks and snacks \\n* Bicycle bags (available at extra cost)\\n* Bike trailer / child seat (book on site)", "exp": "* Discover the hotspots of Luxembourg City.\\n* A fun experience, suitable for all levels.\\n* A combination of Luxembourg's history and modern side", "inc": "* E-bike rental\\n* Local guide\\n* Helmet\\n* Lock", "rest": "* Not recommended for people under 145 cm, neither for people feeling uncomfortable on a bike", "grade": 3, "has_d": 1, "has_f": 0, "has_h": 0, "cutoff": {"type": "before_start_sec", "value": 0}, "images": {"image": [{"url": "https://cdn.tourcms.com/a/12846/13/1/default.jpg", "image_id": 1, "url_large": "https://cdn.tourcms.com/a/12846/13/1/large.jpg", "image_desc": "Route_Image", "url_xlarge": "https://cdn.tourcms.com/a/12846/13/1/xlarge.jpg", "@_thumbnail": "true", "url_thumbnail": "https://cdn.tourcms.com/a/12846/13/1/thumbnail.jpg"}]}, "inc_ex": "* E-bike rental\\n* Local guide\\n* Helmet\\n* Lock", "redeem": "* The guided tour is always in English. \\n* Please note that we can’t guarantee the wished language when going on a group tour.  \\n* Not recommended for people under 145 cm, neither for people feeling uncomfortable on a bike.\\n*  Read the general terms and conditions of our e-Bike tours. \\n* Meeting point: 430-434 Route de Longwy, 1940 Märel Luxemburg, Luxembourg. The welcome is at the front store of sightseeing.lu. The guide will help you with the set-up of your e-bike", "country": "LU", "summary": "Electric bike tour of the city with guide", "tour_id": 13, "book_url": "https://live.tourcms.com/reserve/r1.php?t=13&a=12846&w=13407&people=1&ty=t&k=34360731a15e", "duration": 1, "end_time": "MULTI", "has_sale": 1, "location": "Luxemburg", "longdesc": "After picking up the bikes at our sightseeing.lu store, you will discover the most beautiful places of the capital in a single bike trip. Move around on our latest generation e-bikes to get from one place to another without getting too tired, because this tour doesn’t include any hills… or almost none! Everything is done by elevator or by funicular.  \\n\\n<strong>Your e-bike journey</strong>\\nFrom the city center, you will be directly immersed in the green heart of the city, the Pétrusse Valley with its numerous possibilities to relax in a green area. From there you will be directed to the Grund where you will take the elevator to the Plateau du St. Esprit and the Judicial City – Cité Judiciaire.  From here, you can ride along the Grand Ducal Palace to the historical center and its Herb Market.\\n\\n The Grand-Ducal Palace is the town residence of the Grand-Duke, it has without a doubt one of the most beautiful facades in the city, inspired from Flemish Renaissance of the 16th century. Located in the heart of the city, the palace serves as both a symbolic and functional building. It is the place of official ceremonies, receptions and other important events related to the Grand-Ducal family and the government.\\n\\nFrom the Bock crag, known as “Bockfiels”, you have a wonderful view of the Grund and the Abbey of Neimënster, which you will reach by bike right after. A small trail along the Alzette will lead you to the Rives de Clausen, a popular nightlife spot amongst Luxembourgish people. Continue to the Pfaffenthal until you reach the funicular that will take you to Kirchberg.  \\n\\n <strong>Financial district</strong>\\nContinue to the Pfaffenthal until you reach the funicular that will take you to Kirchberg. You will get out at the foot of the European institutions. Even this imposing alley has its own little park, which you can cross by bike, and then discover the most important buildings of the Luxembourg financial center.  \\n\\n <strong>Modernism\\nThe Kirchberg area combines modernism and antiquity, and nothing is more obvious than the Grand Duke Jean Museum of Modern Art to prove this to you. The Mudam was built on a former military fort which stands out with its imposing glass surfaces on the old 19th century walls.  \\n\\n<strong>End of the tour\\nOnce you’ve passed through, you’ll go back down to the Pfaffenthal to take the panoramic elevator to the gardens of the Pescatore Foundation. From there you will reach the city park and the Kinnekswiss, which announces the end of our e-bike tour through the capital. You will cycle back to the departure point in Merl.\\n\\nIf you wish to go out on an e-bike tour on your own, then check out our self-guided bike tours with the sightseeing.lu app: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=tYGxP1rhr-E", "priority": "MEDIUM", "tour_url": "https://sightseeing.lu/trip/guided-e-bike-tour-the-best-of-luxembourg-in-3-hour/", "validity": {"validity_type": "NOT SET", "validity_value": 0, "validity_minutes": 0}, "available": "Check Availability Calendar", "documents": "", "essential": "* The guided tour is always in English. Please note that we can’t guarantee the wished language when going on a group tour. \\n* You can book your bike tour with insurance for €10. With this insurance you are covered against any damage and/or theft of your bike.\\n* Read the general terms and conditions of our e-Bike tours (see PDF)\\n* Please bring: water bottle and sturdy shoes", "shortdesc": "On this guided tour, we take you to discover the capital’s main points of interest by electric bike. Th