 electric bike. The tour includes some very steep slopes, which is why it is important to be accompanied by an experienced guide	After picking up the bikes at our sightseeing.lu store, you will discover the most beautiful places of the capital in a single bike trip. Move around on our latest generation e-bikes to get from one place to another without getting too tired, because this tour doesn’t include any hills… or almost none! Everything is done by elevator or by funicular.  \n\n<strong>Your e-bike journey</strong>\nFrom the city center, you will be directly immersed in the green heart of the city, the Pétrusse Valley with its numerous possibilities to relax in a green area. From there you will be directed to the Grund where you will take the elevator to the Plateau du St. Esprit and the Judicial City – Cité Judiciaire.  From here, you can ride along the Grand Ducal Palace to the historical center and its Herb Market.\n\n The Grand-Ducal Palace is the town residence of the Grand-Duke, it has without a doubt one of the most beautiful facades in the city, inspired from Flemish Renaissance of the 16th century. Located in the heart of the city, the palace serves as both a symbolic and functional building. It is the place of official ceremonies, receptions and other important events related to the Grand-Ducal family and the government.\n\nFrom the Bock crag, known as “Bockfiels”, you have a wonderful view of the Grund and the Abbey of Neimënster, which you will reach by bike right after. A small trail along the Alzette will lead you to the Rives de Clausen, a popular nightlife spot amongst Luxembourgish people. Continue to the Pfaffenthal until you reach the funicular that will take you to Kirchberg.  \n\n <strong>Financial district</strong>\nContinue to the Pfaffenthal until you reach the funicular that will take you to Kirchberg. You will get out at the foot of the European institutions. Even this imposing alley has its own little park, which you can cross by bike, and then discover the most important buildings of the Luxembourg financial center.  \n\n <strong>Modernism\nThe Kirchberg area combines modernism and antiquity, and nothing is more obvious than the Grand Duke Jean Museum of Modern Art to prove this to you. The Mudam was built on a former military fort which stands out with its imposing glass surfaces on the old 19th century walls.  \n\n<strong>End of the tour\nOnce you’ve passed through, you’ll go back down to the Pfaffenthal to take the panoramic elevator to the gardens of the Pescatore Foundation. From there you will reach the city park and the Kinnekswiss, which announces the end of our e-bike tour through the capital. You will cycle back to the departure point in Merl.\n\nIf you wish to go out on an e-bike tour on your own, then check out our self-guided bike tours with the sightseeing.lu app: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=tYGxP1rhr-E	* Discover the hotspots of Luxembourg City.\n* A fun experience, suitable for all levels.\n* A combination of Luxembourg's history and modern side	{"E-bike rental","Local guide",Helmet,Lock}	{"Drinks and snacks","Bicycle bags (available at extra cost)","Bike trailer / child seat (book on site)"}	* The guided tour is always in English. Please note that we can’t guarantee the wished language when going on a group tour. \n* You can book your bike tour with insurance for €10. With this insurance you are covered against any damage and/or theft of your bike.\n* Read the general terms and conditions of our e-Bike tours (see PDF)\n* Please bring: water bottle and sturdy shoes	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	1	10	f	2026-05-23	2026-11-29
tcms_21	21	Entry Ticket to Chateau de Larochette	\N	Visit the Larochette Castle, one of the most picturesque medieval sites in Luxembourg, a ruin overlooking the city at about 50 metres high. The Larochette Castle is one of the most picturesque medieval sites in Luxembourg – a dramatic ruin full of history and legends. The castle sits on a sandstone promontory overlooking Larochette, dominating the valley	\N	7.00	\N	Varies	Tours	{}	Luxembourg	Sightseeing.lu	https://cdn.tourcms.com/a/12846/21/1/xlarge.jpg	{https://cdn.tourcms.com/a/12846/21/1/xlarge.jpg,https://cdn.tourcms.com/a/12846/21/2/xlarge.jpg}	{"Experience one of the most enchanting castles in Luxembourg,","Stunning views over the valley,","A unique environment in a small fortified village,","A castle full of legends and myths"}	\N	0.00	0	https://live.tourcms.com/reserve/r1.php?t=21&a=12846&w=13407&people=1&ty=t&k=0108fe366012	\N	f	f	published	{"ex": "* Guide (can be booked separately)", "exp": "* Experience one of the most enchanting castles in Luxembourg,\\n* Stunning views over the valley,\\n* A unique environment in a small fortified village,\\n* A castle full of legends and myths", "inc": "* Access to the castle", "grade": 1, "has_d": 1, "has_f": 0, "has_h": 0, "cutoff": {"type": "before_start_sec", "value": 0}, "images": {"image": [{"url": "https://cdn.tourcms.com/a/12846/21/1/default.jpg", "image_id": 1, "url_large": "https://cdn.tourcms.com/a/12846/21/1/large.jpg", "image_desc": "Route_Image", "url_xlarge": "https://cdn.tourcms.com/a/12846/21/1/xlarge.jpg", "@_thumbnail": "true", "url_thumbnail": "https://cdn.tourcms.com/a/12846/21/1/thumbnail.jpg"}, {"url": "https://cdn.tourcms.com/a/12846/21/2/default.jpg", "image_id": 2, "url_large": "https://cdn.tourcms.com/a/12846/21/2/large.jpg", "image_desc": "Route_Image", "url_xlarge": "https://cdn.tourcms.com/a/12846/21/2/xlarge.jpg", "url_thumbnail": "https://cdn.tourcms.com/a/12846/21/2/thumbnail.jpg"}]}, "inc_ex": "* Access to the castle", "redeem": "* The castle is open from March to November, 7 days a week.\\n* Opening: 10 am to 6 pm. (Last admission at 5 pm)", "country": "LU", "summary": "Visit the medieval Larochette Castle ruins", "tour_id": 21, "book_url": "https://live.tourcms.com/reserve/r1.php?t=21&a=12846&w=13407&people=1&ty=t&k=0108fe366012", "duration": 1, "end_time": "MULTI", "has_sale": 1, "location": "Luxembourg", "longdesc": "The ruins of Larochette Castle tower above the village from a sandstone rock spur about 50 metres high, known as the “Elsebeth” plateau. Their advanced state of ruin is largely due to a fire that devastated the castle around 1565. \\nThe first traces of occupation on this site go back to the 8th century, when a refuge was built on the rock. The first stone castle was constructed in the 12th century. At that time it was surrounded by a fortified enclosure, only accessible through a large outer bailey, itself protected by an earthen rampart dating from the first half of the 11the century. \\nThe name \\"La Rochete\\" appears in 1241, when an Arnould, lord of the place, is mentioned a a witness in a charter issued by Henry, count of Luxembourg. \\nThe seigniorial family of Larochette descended from a very old noble family from Ouren, south of Saint-Vith in present-day Belgium. As early as 1176, an “Arnoldus de Rupe” is cited as a witness in a donation charter under Count Henry I. Over the following centuries, the lords of Larochette continued to play an important role in the regional nobility, especially at the time when the duke of Luxembourg became king of Bohemia and later emperor of the Holy Roman Empire. \\nAfter 1348, the castle estate was gradually divided among several heirs. During the following century, at least five manor houses were built within the castle walls. Two of them are still known by name today: the House of Homburg and the House of Créhange. Repeated divisions of inheritance in the 15ᵗʰ and 16ᵗʰ centuries (Fels-Ouren, Fels-Trier, Fels-Heffingen and Fels-Heffingen-Contern) led to a highly fragmented ownership. The site ceased to be permanently inhabited, fell into disuse and gradually lost its military importance.  In 1979, the Luxembourg State signed an emphyteutic lease with the then count of Fels. Finally, in June 2020, the State acquired Larochette Castle in order to restore, secure and enhance it for visitors", "priority": "MEDIUM", "tour_url": "https://sightseeing.lu/trip/entry-ticket-to-chateau-de-larochette/", "validity": {"validity_type": "NOT SET", "validity_value": 0, "validity_minutes": 0}, "available": "Check Availability Calendar", "documents": "", "essential": "* The castle is open from March to November, 7 days a week.\\n* Opening: 10 am to 6 pm. (Last admission at 5 pm)\\n* Situation of disability: the castle can be visited under certain circumstances. Send an email to contact@larochette-castle.lu\\n* Dogs are welcome on the castle grounds but must be kept on a leash", "shortdesc": "Visit the Larochette Castle, one of the most picturesque medieval sites in Luxembourg, a ruin overlooking the city at about 50 metres high. The Larochette Castle is one of the most picturesque medieval sites in Luxembourg – a dramatic ruin full of history and legends. The castle sits on a sandstone promontory overlooking Larochette, dominating the valley", "time_type": "strict", "tour_name": "Entry Ticket to Chateau de Larochette", "tour_tags": {"tag": [{"text": "Activity is suitable for adults only", "token": "adults-only", "value": 0}, {"text": "Activity is largely centered around animals", "token": "animals", "value": 0}, {"text": "Tour is guided by pre-recorded commentary", "token": "audio-guide", "value": 0}, {"text": "Activity visits or happens at a beach", "token": "beaches", "value": 0}, {"text": "Tour involves sightseeing by bicycle", "token": "bike-tours", "value": 0}, {"text": "Tour involves sightseeing by boat", "token": "boat-tours", "value": 0}, {"text": "Card or pass that offers admission to multiple top attrac