roughout experience"}, {"name": "regularly_sanitized", "value": "NOTSET", "display_name": "Regularly sanitized high-traffic areas"}, {"name": "equipment_sanitized", "value": "NOTSET", "display_name": "Gear/equipment sanitized between use"}, {"name": "transportation_vehicles_sanitized", "value": "NOTSET", "display_name": "Transportation vehicles regularly sanitized"}, {"name": "guides_required_to_wash_hands", "value": "NOTSET", "display_name": "Guides required to wash hands"}, {"name": "temperature_checks_for_staff", "value": "NOTSET", "display_name": "Regular temperature checks for staff"}, {"name": "temperature_checks_for_travelers", "value": "NOTSET", "display_name": "Temperature checks for travelers upon arrival"}, {"name": "contactless_payments_for_extras", "value": "NOTSET", "display_name": "Contactless payments for gratuities and add-ons"}]}, "pickup_on_request": 0, "redemption_method": "", "suitable_for_solo": 0, "from_price_display": "&#8364;7", "last_bookable_date": "2026-11-15", "next_bookable_date": "2026-05-22", "supplier_tour_code": "PALISIS_55_12422", "cancellation_policy": "", "geocode_start_point": {"label": "Larochette Castle", "geocode": "49.785376,6.217503", "loc_relation": 1, "google_place_id": "ChIJw6lsWuFZlUcR4A_M2jcYdvg"}, "suitable_for_groups": 0, "suitable_for_couples": 0, "suitable_for_business": 0, "suitable_for_children": 0, "suitable_for_students": 0, "default_departure_size": 20, "from_price_apr_display": "&#8364;0", "from_price_aug_display": "&#8364;7", "from_price_dec_display": "&#8364;0", "from_price_feb_display": "&#8364;0", "from_price_jan_display": "&#8364;0", "from_price_jul_display": "&#8364;7", "from_price_jun_display": "&#8364;7", "from_price_mar_display": "&#8364;0", "from_price_may_display": "&#8364;7", "from_price_nov_display": "&#8364;7", "from_price_oct_display": "&#8364;7", "from_price_sep_display": "&#8364;7", "tour_permit_child_only": 0, "distribution_identifier": "SI_12846_21", "suitable_for_wheelchairs": 0, "tour_departure_structure": {"type": "NOTSET"}, "descriptions_last_updated": "2026-05-19"}	2026-05-22 07:25:14.617+00	palisis	\N	\N	2026-05-12 12:31:19.639379+00	2026-05-22 07:25:14.618602+00	Day tour/trip/activity/attraction - No overnight stay	4	Independent / Self-drive	All ages / Not applicable	No accommodation / Not applicable	{operator-direct-product,entrance-ticket}	{}	Larochette Castle	49.785376,6.217503	Larochette Castle	49.785376,6.217503	LU	MEDIUM	Visit the Larochette Castle, one of the most picturesque medieval sites in Luxembourg, a ruin overlooking the city at about 50 metres high. The Larochette Castle is one of the most picturesque medieval sites in Luxembourg – a dramatic ruin full of history and legends. The castle sits on a sandstone promontory overlooking Larochette, dominating the valley	The ruins of Larochette Castle tower above the village from a sandstone rock spur about 50 metres high, known as the “Elsebeth” plateau. Their advanced state of ruin is largely due to a fire that devastated the castle around 1565. \nThe first traces of occupation on this site go back to the 8th century, when a refuge was built on the rock. The first stone castle was constructed in the 12th century. At that time it was surrounded by a fortified enclosure, only accessible through a large outer bailey, itself protected by an earthen rampart dating from the first half of the 11the century. \nThe name "La Rochete" appears in 1241, when an Arnould, lord of the place, is mentioned a a witness in a charter issued by Henry, count of Luxembourg. \nThe seigniorial family of Larochette descended from a very old noble family from Ouren, south of Saint-Vith in present-day Belgium. As early as 1176, an “Arnoldus de Rupe” is cited as a witness in a donation charter under Count Henry I. Over the following centuries, the lords of Larochette continued to play an important role in the regional nobility, especially at the time when the duke of Luxembourg became king of Bohemia and later emperor of the Holy Roman Empire. \nAfter 1348, the castle estate was gradually divided among several heirs. During the following century, at least five manor houses were built within the castle walls. Two of them are still known by name today: the House of Homburg and the House of Créhange. Repeated divisions of inheritance in the 15ᵗʰ and 16ᵗʰ centuries (Fels-Ouren, Fels-Trier, Fels-Heffingen and Fels-Heffingen-Contern) led to a highly fragmented ownership. The site ceased to be permanently inhabited, fell into disuse and gradually lost its military importance.  In 1979, the Luxembourg State signed an emphyteutic lease with the then count of Fels. Finally, in June 2020, the State acquired Larochette Castle in order to restore, secure and enhance it for visitors	* Experience one of the most enchanting castles in Luxembourg,\n* Stunning views over the valley,\n* A unique environment in a small fortified village,\n* A castle full of legends and myths	{"Access to the castle"}	{"Guide (can be booked separately)"}	* The castle is open from March to November, 7 days a week.\n* Opening: 10 am to 6 pm. (Last admission at 5 pm)\n* Situation of disability: the castle can be visited under certain circumstances. Send an email to contact@larochette-castle.lu\n* Dogs are welcome on the castle grounds but must be kept on a leash	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	1	10	f	2026-05-22	2026-11-15
tcms_22	22	Entry Ticket to Chateau de Beaufort	\N	Explore the Beaufort Castle- two historic buildings with the ruins of a medieval castle and a 17th century residence built on the rock above the fortress. Enjoy the magnificent town of Beaufort, a place where nature and history come together beautifully	\N	8.00	\N	Varies	Tours	{}	Luxembourg	Sightseeing.lu	https://cdn.tourcms.com/a/12846/22/1/xlarge.jpg	{https://cdn.tourcms.com/a/12846/22/1/xlarge.jpg,https://cdn.tourcms.com/a/12846/22/2/xlarge.jpg,https://cdn.tourcms.com/a/12846/22/3/xlarge.jpg}	{"Beaufort Castle, a picturesque ruin of the 11th century.","Admire a 17th century residence built on a rock.","Step into a fairytale environment surrounded by towers, walls and courtyards.","Enjoy a traditional blackcurrant liqueur produced locally"}	\N	0.00	0	https://live.tourcms.com/reserve/r1.php?t=22&a=12846&w=13407&people=1&ty=t&k=b2ec66423223	\N	f	f	published	{"ex": "* Guide (bookable at a different price)", "exp": "* Beaufort Castle, a picturesque ruin of the 11th century.\\n* Admire a 17th century residence built on a rock.\\n* Step into a fairytale environment surrounded by towers, walls and courtyards.\\n* Enjoy a traditional blackcurrant liqueur produced locally", "inc": "* Access to the castle \\n* For adults: a tasting of the Cassero blackcurrant liqueur is included in the admission ticket.​​​", "rest": "* The medieval castle is not accessible by wheelchair\\n* Dogs are welcome on the medieval ruins grounds but must be kept on a leash. However, no dogs are permitted during the guided tours of the 17th-century residence. Guided tours are offered daily in various languages. They are announced at the ticket office on the day of the tour", "grade": 1, "has_d": 1, "has_f": 0, "has_h": 0, "cutoff": {"type": "before_start_sec", "value": 0}, "images": {"image": [{"url": "https://cdn.tourcms.com/a/12846/22/1/default.jpg", "image_id": 1, "url_large": "https://cdn.tourcms.com/a/12846/22/1/large.jpg", "image_desc": "Route_Image", "url_xlarge": "https://cdn.tourcms.com/a/12846/22/1/xlarge.jpg", "@_thumbnail": "true", "url_thumbnail": "https://cdn.tourcms.com/a/12846/22/1/thumbnail.jpg"}, {"url": "https://cdn.tourcms.com/a/12846/22/2/default.jpg", "image_id": 2, "url_large": "https://cdn.tourcms.com/a/12846/22/2/large.jpg", "image_desc": "Route_Image", "url_xlarge": "https://cdn.tourcms.com/a/12846/22/2/xlarge.jpg", "url_thumbnail": "https://cdn.tourcms.com/a/12846/22/2/thumbnail.jpg"}, {"url": "https://cdn.tourcms.com/a/12846/22/3/default.jpg", "image_id": 3, "url_large": "https://cdn.tourcms.com/a/12846/22/3/large.jpg", "image_desc": "Route_Image", "url_xlarge": "https://cdn.tourcms.com/a/12846/22/3/xlarge.jpg", "url_thumbnail": "https://cdn.tourcms.com/a/12846/22/3/thumbnail.jpg"}]}, "inc_ex": "* Access to the castle \\n* For adults: a tasting of the Cassero blackcurrant liqueur is included in the admission ticket.​​​", "country": "LU", "summary": "Explore Beaufort Castle and historic town", "tour_id": 22, "book_url": "https://live.tourcms.com/reserve/r1.php?t=22&a=12846&w=13407&people=1&ty=t&k=b2ec66423223", "duration": 1, "end_time": "MULTI", "has_sale": 1, "location": "Luxembourg", "longdesc": "The Beaufort estate is made up of two historic buildings: the ruins of a medieval castle and a 17ᵗʰ-century residence built on the rock above the fortress.\\nThe medieval castle was extended in several stages between the 11ᵗʰ and 17ᵗʰ centuries. Over time it changed owners many times, and each of them left their mark. This is why you can see towers, windows and walls from different periods side by side.\\nIn 1639, Baron Jean de Beck, governor of the Duchy of Luxembourg in the service of King Philip IV of Spain, bought the medieval castle from a ruined owner. He started the construction of the new residence overlooking the old fortress.\\nWork on this manor house began in 1643 and was completed in 1649. Jean de Beck died in captivity in 1648 and never saw the building finished.\\nLater, the 