astle Beaufort	49.833674,6.286608	LU	MEDIUM	Explore the Beaufort Castle- two historic buildings with the ruins of a medieval castle and a 17th century residence built on the rock above the fortress. Enjoy the magnificent town of Beaufort, a place where nature and history come together beautifully	The Beaufort estate is made up of two historic buildings: the ruins of a medieval castle and a 17ᵗʰ-century residence built on the rock above the fortress.\nThe medieval castle was extended in several stages between the 11ᵗʰ and 17ᵗʰ centuries. Over time it changed owners many times, and each of them left their mark. This is why you can see towers, windows and walls from different periods side by side.\nIn 1639, Baron Jean de Beck, governor of the Duchy of Luxembourg in the service of King Philip IV of Spain, bought the medieval castle from a ruined owner. He started the construction of the new residence overlooking the old fortress.\nWork on this manor house began in 1643 and was completed in 1649. Jean de Beck died in captivity in 1648 and never saw the building finished.\nLater, the house was more than just a residence: over the centuries it was used as a military barracks, a farm and an industrial site.\nIn 1932, Edmond Linckels, the last private owner of the estate, opened the medieval castle to visitors. That same year, he launched the production of Cassero, a blackcurrant liqueur that is still made today in the cellars of the 17ᵗʰ-century residence	* Beaufort Castle, a picturesque ruin of the 11th century.\n* Admire a 17th century residence built on a rock.\n* Step into a fairytale environment surrounded by towers, walls and courtyards.\n* Enjoy a traditional blackcurrant liqueur produced locally	{"Access to the castle","For adults: a tasting of the Cassero blackcurrant liqueur is included in the admission ticket.​​​"}	{"Guide (bookable at a different price)"}	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	1	10	f	2026-05-22	2026-11-15
tcms_25	25	Boat ticket - M.S. Princesse Marie-Astrid	\N	Step aboard the M.S. “Princesse Marie-Astrid” for a pleasant cruise on the Moselle between Remich and Schengen. Discover the magnificent vineyards of the Luxembourg–France–Germany tri-border region, as well as the Haff Réimech nature reserve.	\N	12.00	\N	1h20	Tours	{}	Luxembourg	Sightseeing.lu	https://cdn.tourcms.com/a/12846/25/1/large.png	{https://cdn.tourcms.com/a/12846/25/1/large.png}	{"Cruise aboard the M.S. “Princesse Marie-Astrid”,","Explore the Moselle wine region,","Journey through the Three-Border Region – Luxembourg – Germany – France,","A relaxing atmosphere and exceptional views."}	\N	0.00	0	https://live.tourcms.com/reserve/r1.php?t=25&a=12846&w=13407&people=1&ty=t&k=21e42096d06a	\N	t	f	published	{"ex": "Meal and drinks", "exp": "Cruise aboard the M.S. “Princesse Marie-Astrid”,\\nExplore the Moselle wine region,\\nJourney through the Three-Border Region – Luxembourg – Germany – France,\\nA relaxing atmosphere and exceptional views.", "inc": "Boat ticket", "grade": 1, "has_d": 1, "has_f": 0, "has_h": 0, "cutoff": {"type": "before_start_sec", "value": 0}, "images": {"image": [{"url": "https://cdn.tourcms.com/a/12846/25/1/default.png", "image_id": 1, "url_large": "https://cdn.tourcms.com/a/12846/25/1/large.png", "@_thumbnail": "true", "url_thumbnail": "https://cdn.tourcms.com/a/12846/25/1/thumbnail.png"}]}, "inc_ex": "Boat ticket", "country": "LU", "summary": "A peaceful and friendly atmosphere - the ideal getaway to enjoy the beauty of the Moselle, combining nature, relaxation and wine-growing traditions.", "tour_id": 25, "book_url": "https://live.tourcms.com/reserve/r1.php?t=25&a=12846&w=13407&people=1&ty=t&k=21e42096d06a", "duration": 1, "end_time": "MULTI", "has_sale": 1, "location": "Luxembourg", "longdesc": "Discover an unforgettable cruise on the Moselle aboard the M.S. “Princesse Marie-Astrid”, an experience characterised by relaxation, nature and exceptional views.\\nSetting off from the town of Remich, the boat sails peacefully to Schengen, an iconic spot in the “Land of Three Borders” between Luxembourg, Germany and France. Throughout the journey, you’ll admire the magnificent vineyards that line the Moselle and have shaped the region’s landscape and wine-making tradition for centuries.\\nOne of the highlights of this cruise is the passage past the Haff Réimech nature reserve. This protected site captivates visitors with its ecological richness and the beauty of its flora and fauna. In this peaceful atmosphere, with a bit of luck, you’ll be able to spot numerous waterbirds whilst enjoying the calm of the river.\\nWith its idyllic landscapes, cultural richness and friendly atmosphere, this cruise on the Moselle offers a break filled with serenity and discovery. Take a seat on the upper deck, savor a glass of fine local wine and let yourself be charmed by the riverbanks gently passing before your eyes.\\nAn invitation to discover the Moselle in a different light, amidst nature, traditions and the European art of living.", "priority": "MEDIUM", "tour_url": "https://sightseeing.lu/blog/", "validity": {"validity_type": "NOT SET", "validity_value": 0, "validity_minutes": 0}, "available": "check timetable", "documents": "", "essential": "Departure from Remich at 3.00 pm, - Meeting Point: Quai – Esplanade de la Moselle,\\nBoarding from 2.30 pm", "shortdesc": "Step aboard the M.S. “Princesse Marie-Astrid” for a pleasant cruise on the Moselle between Remich and Schengen. Discover the magnificent vineyards of the Luxembourg–France–Germany tri-border region, as well as the Haff Réimech nature reserve.", "time_type": "strict", "tour_name": "Boat ticket - M.S. Princesse Marie-Astrid", "tour_tags": {"tag": [{"text": "Activity is suitable for adults only", "token": "adults-only", "value": 0}, {"text": "Activity is largely centered around animals", "token": "animals", "value": 0}, {"text": "Tour is guided by pre-recorded commentary", "token": "audio-guide", "value": 0}