7+00	2026-05-26 14:46:07.141769+00	Day tour/trip/activity/attraction - No overnight stay	4	Not applicable	All ages / Not applicable	No accommodation / Not applicable	{}	{}	Quai Remich – Esplanade de la Moselle	49.542197,6.367509	\N	49.542197,6.367509	LU	MEDIUM	Step aboard the M.S. “Princesse Marie-Astrid” for a pleasant cruise on the Moselle between Remich and Schengen. Discover the magnificent vineyards of the Luxembourg–France–Germany tri-border region, as well as the Haff Réimech nature reserve.	Discover an unforgettable cruise on the Moselle aboard the M.S. “Princesse Marie-Astrid”, an experience characterised by relaxation, nature and exceptional views.\nSetting off from the town of Remich, the boat sails peacefully to Schengen, an iconic spot in the “Land of Three Borders” between Luxembourg, Germany and France. Throughout the journey, you’ll admire the magnificent vineyards that line the Moselle and have shaped the region’s landscape and wine-making tradition for centuries.\nOne of the highlights of this cruise is the passage past the Haff Réimech nature reserve. This protected site captivates visitors with its ecological richness and the beauty of its flora and fauna. In this peaceful atmosphere, with a bit of luck, you’ll be able to spot numerous waterbirds whilst enjoying the calm of the river.\nWith its idyllic landscapes, cultural richness and friendly atmosphere, this cruise on the Moselle offers a break filled with serenity and discovery. Take a seat on the upper deck, savor a glass of fine local wine and let yourself be charmed by the riverbanks gently passing before your eyes.\nAn invitation to discover the Moselle in a different light, amidst nature, traditions and the European art of living.	Cruise aboard the M.S. “Princesse Marie-Astrid”,\nExplore the Moselle wine region,\nJourney through the Three-Border Region – Luxembourg – Germany – France,\nA relaxing atmosphere and exceptional views.	{"Boat ticket"}	{"Meal and drinks"}	Departure from Remich at 3.00 pm, - Meeting Point: Quai – Esplanade de la Moselle,\nBoarding from 2.30 pm	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	1	10	f	2026-05-24	2026-09-13
